  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "A recent survey focused on LLMs proposed a taxonomy specific to these models (Gallegos et al., 2024).",
    "It lists more than half a dozen possible ways to discriminate against someone using language, ranging from erasure (omission of the idiolect of a group) to stereotyping (false, immutable association of a group to a property) to differential recognition of forms of speech.",
    "The consequences can be important, as they affect hiring practices, access to markets (such as credit, housing) or to services, and other aspects of life.",
    "In our case, the effects seem less dire.",
    "After all, if the model displays biases, the main consequence should (hopefully) be that LLMs won't be used in lieu of human research subjects."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "A recent survey focused on LLMs proposed a taxonomy specific to these models (Gallegos et al., 2024)."
  ]
}